Kurtz
This must be the Talking Island.
This was told by one who trained in the House of the Red Knight, so I am sure that this information is correct.
It is also true that those who oppose his majesty's rule live here.
But surely his majesty is over reacting! Even though he is the son of Duke Dephil, he is only a child.
Watch your mouth. Do you think you are in the position to question his majesty's orders?
I...I've committed a capital crime!
Okay, let us scout around the island first. Remember, do not draw your sword unless necessary.
Yes!
I think it would be faster to contact and hire an informant among the island people.
Wouldn't it be better to find Gunter and ask him?
Gunter is not on good terms with his majesty. What makes you think he will help us?
Why don't we just kill everybody on this island, including Gunter? Then there won't be any trouble left.
Didn't I tell you to watch your mouth? I assure you, anyone spilling innocent blood will pay ten times as much.
The problem is... does the person we're looking for have any influence on this island?
No, it is the other way around. If someone here is influencing the people, then he could be the one who is most likely to oppose his majesty. Now, stay alert and be cautious!
Yes!
Let's hear the inquiry report.
Yes! No one particularly suspicious looking up 'til now.
But it seems that the people of this island are generally opposed to his majesty.
We were almost attacked once while scouting.
We haven't found anyone particularly special. In other words, everyone here is a little suspicious!
Hmm. Then we must continue to watch this island.
Okay, we are retiring for today. Everyone, withdraw!
Yes!
How dare you be so rude!
You are so pitiful that you can't even recognize your enemy's skill.
Urgh!
Hmph, you may have killed me, but it's no use. I have already informed his majesty that traitors are on this island. A new expedition will come soon.
